title: 2015 BRD Năstase Țiriac Trophy – Doubles
text:
<a href="Jean-Julien%20Rojer">Jean-Julien Rojer</a> and <a href="Horia%20Tec%C4%83u">Horia Tecău</a> were the defending champions, but withdrew before their first-round match because of Tecău's right forearm injury.<br>
<a href="Marius%20Copil">Marius Copil</a> and <a href="Adrian%20Ungur">Adrian Ungur</a> won the title, defeating <a href="Nicholas%20Monroe">Nicholas Monroe</a> and <a href="Artem%20Sitak">Artem Sitak</a> in the final, 3–6, 7–5, [17–15].
